    "If you estimate a function that perfectly predicts all values it incorporates noise. The bias is the difference between the predicted and the real value. The more accurate the prediction the lower the bias but the higher the variance of the prediction function."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The prediction of house prices we've done does not predict every single house price precisely. This difference between the predicted house price and the real house price is the bias. In this case the bias is high, but the variance of the prediction function low. Improving the fit will result in a lower bias but a higher variance as \"the curves move along the values\"."
   ]
